### Phase 5 — API Gateway end-to-end smoke test
###
### Now everything goes through `gatewayUrl` (localhost:8080). Backend services
### are only reachable directly via authUrl/appUrl/executionUrl when debugging.
###
### Prerequisites:
###   - make gateway-redis-up   (Redis for rate limiting)
###   - make execution-db-up    (Postgres)
###   - make app-db-up          (MongoDB shared by auth + app)
###   - make judge0-tunnel      (Judge0 reachable on localhost:2358)
###   - auth-service running on :8083 (default)
###   - execution-service running on :8081
###   - app-service running on :8082
###   - api-gateway running on :8080
###   - make app-seed
###
### Trust boundary check: there is NO X-User-Id in any request below — the
### gateway sets it after validating the JWT. If a downstream service receives
### an unauthorized request through the gateway, that's a bug.
###

### 1. Register through gateway (public bypass — no token required) → 201
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/api/v1/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "phase5tester@example.com",
  "username": "phase5tester",
  "password": "supersecret123"
}

> {%
    if (response.status === 201) {
      client.global.set("accessToken", response.body.accessToken);
    }
%}

### 2. Login through gateway (public bypass) → 200 + tokens
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "emailOrUsername": "phase5tester@example.com",
  "password": "supersecret123"
}

> {%
    client.global.set("accessToken", response.body.accessToken);
    client.global.set("refreshToken", response.body.refreshToken);
%}

### 3. /auth/me through gateway — JWT validated, X-User-Id injected → 200
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/api/v1/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

> {%
    client.global.set("userId", response.body.id);
%}

### 4. List problems through gateway — JWT required (app route) → 200
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/api/v1/problems
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

> {%
    client.global.set("problemId", response.body[0].id);
    client.global.set("problemSlug", response.body[0].slug);
%}

### 5. Get problem detail through gateway → 200
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/api/v1/problems/{{problemSlug}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 6. Submit code through gateway — gateway injects X-User-Id, App accepts → 202
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/api/v1/submissions
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "problemId": "{{problemId}}",
  "languageId": 71,
  "sourceCode": "print('Hello from Phase 5 gateway!')",
  "customStdin": null
}

> {%
    client.global.set("submissionId", response.body.submissionId);
%}

### 7. Poll submission through gateway → 200
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/api/v1/submissions/{{submissionId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 8. Stats through gateway → 200
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/api/v1/users/me/stats
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###
### Negative tests — gateway must enforce auth before the request reaches
### any backend service.
###

### 9. Missing Authorization on protected route → 401 from gateway
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/api/v1/problems

### 10. Garbage Bearer token → 401 from gateway (signature check fails)
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/api/v1/problems
Authorization: Bearer not.a.real.token

### 11. Tampered token → 401 from gateway
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/api/v1/problems
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}xxx

### 12. Spoofed X-User-Id on a public path is stripped by the gateway,
###     so the request reaches /auth/register without it. Should still 409
###     (user already exists from step 1) — proves the public bypass strips
###     the spoofed header rather than trusting it.
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/api/v1/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Id: 1234567890abcdef12345678

{
  "email": "phase5tester@example.com",
  "username": "phase5tester",
  "password": "supersecret123"
}

###
### Rate limit demo — fire repeatedly. Auth route is 5/min per IP.
### After ~10 (initial burst) you should start seeing 429s.
###

### 13. Hammer login — eventually returns 429
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "emailOrUsername": "phase5tester@example.com",
  "password": "wrong-password"
}

### 14. Gateway health (public)
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/actuator/health

### 15. Correlation id propagates: send one, expect it back on the response
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/api/v1/problems
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
X-Correlation-Id: phase5-smoke-test-001
